Read 05: Images, Color, Text

Summary:
Images:
1.	<img> element adds images.
2.	src attribute indicates the source of an image
3.	alt attribute describes the content of an image.

Color:
1.	RGB values, hex codes, and color names are three ways to specify colors in CSS.
2.	Color picker helps in finding colors.
3.	RGBA indicates opacity.
4.	HSL with an optional opacity value is HSLA.
Text:
1.	font, size, weight, style, and spacing can be controlled with properties.
2.	Right license is needed to use a wider range of typefaces.
3.	Pseudo-classes can be used to change the style of an element when a user hovers over or clicks on text, or when they have visited a link.
